# Pre-commit secret-scan baseline.
#
# One fingerprint per line, format: <path>:<pattern>:<token-sha256-prefix>.
# (Content-based — entries survive edits that shift line numbers; the
# 12-hex-char prefix is a SHA-256 of the matched token, so no secret-
# shaped strings ever land in this file.)
# Comment lines (start with '#') and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Use this file ONLY for confirmed false positives — never to silence a
# real key. Rotate first, fingerprint second.
#
# To add a fingerprint, copy it verbatim from the scanner's stderr block
# (the "Fingerprints (for .secrets-baseline):" section).
#
# Alternative: add `# pragma: secret-scan-allow` to the offending line
# for one-off opt-outs that don't deserve a baseline entry.
